Spec: Check Update Command
Purpose:
  Check whether a newer SpecDD release is available for the current project.

Structure:
  check-update.ts: Check update command implementation.
  check-update.test.ts: Check update command tests.

Owns:
  check-update.ts
  check-update.test.ts

References:
  ../container.sdd
  ../services/update-checker/service.sdd

Must:
  Expose a factory for the check-update command.
  Receive a Container-compatible dependency object.
  Set a concise command description for help output.
  Use the current working directory as the check target.
  Call UpdateChecker.check with the current working directory.
  Exit with code 0 when no update is available.
  Exit with code 1 when an update is available.
  Include the project copyright notice in help output.
  Include SpecDD framework and CLI project help links in help output.
  Support construction by the Container.

Must not:
  Construct application services.
  Accept a target path argument.
  Download, verify, apply, or modify distributions directly.
  Implement the CLI entrypoint.

Depends on:
  commander
  Container
  UpdateChecker
  process exit code handling

Exposes:
  createCheckUpdateCommand(container)

Accepts:
  no command arguments

Returns:
  commander Command
